its a beautiful place and a tourist scam
Jul 2014 ‚Ä¢ Family
Lets start with the positive. Halong Bay is stunning and a real treat to the eyes. Now , on to the negatives : you have seen it better online and in the movies before! All boats have to stop in the same bay ( government regulations), all tourists go swim on the same disgustingly polluted and tiny beach, go kayaking in the same place. And oh, by the way, right before he shows you where to go, the guide lightly specifies that it is pointless to try to fish because its been a long time since the squids have disappeared. You will also visit the same underground cave....And will not be allowed to jump from the boat. No matter which boat you choose, you will experience the same "disaster in the making". As to the boats, the sleeping arrangements and the quality of the food will vary based on the price you are ready to pay. More expensive oats have fewer cabins so there will be fewer of you taking the same shot at 5am ( and no, dont think of taking a kayak in the morning, it is not part of the programme!).
Dont get me wrong, it might be the best thing ever for the Halong Bay that tourists are confined to a filthy , tiny portion of it. It may help the rest of the Bay to remain untouched - or at least I would hope so - but it surely makes fro a very poor experience. What is left? Either you go and see it for yourself. Or you dont go and will probably regret it forever. Try to go for a day without sleeping there?( I am not sure this is possible?) it would certainly not have been practical for us with 3 young kids and with a lengthy time to get to and from Halong bay being significant from Hanoi. In any case, 2 nights there is one night too many!
