Go for two nights with Canary cruises
Aug 2013 ‚Ä¢ Couples
Don't even think of doing a Halong bay cruise for only one night, you will miss the best part. It is a four hour drive at least from Hanoi and to have to come back the next day cannot be fun. On your extra day you get to see the less touristy and crowded bit, the real wonder and beauty of the islands. We went on a two night cruise with Canary cruises and can highly recommend them, excellent facilities and staff and the food! Oh my, words cannot describe the assortment of dishes and the flavours, even the food on the extra day,that they take you on a smaller boat, is exceptional. They even cater for special dietary needs, however small. Yes, some of the attractions, like the Surprise cave ins crowded but is still worth a visit. The staff is very friendly and helpfull and our guide, Hub, is passionate about his job and his country, he is full of interesting bits of information. If there is one negative : they gave us knives and forks to eat with and not chopsticks, we want chopsticks in Vietnam.
